summary.name: Gapminder Dataset
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about countries' population, life expectancy, and fertility rates over time.

properties.description: The year in which the data was recorded.
A cluster number assigned to the country based on its characteristics.
The average life expectancy of the country's population.
The average number of children born to a woman in the country.

goals.question: What is the trend of population over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of population against year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if the population of countries in the dataset is increasing, decreasing or remaining constant over time.

goals.question: What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of life expectancy against fertility rate
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a correlation between life expectancy and fertility rate in the countries in the dataset.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of life expectancy values in the dataset and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rate across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of fertility rate values in the dataset and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: How does the population of countries in different clusters compare?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of population against cluster
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there are any significant differences in population between countries in different clusters.

code:
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data, ci=None, estimator='median')
    median_pop = data['pop'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_pop, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Population: {median_pop:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='life_expect', y='fertility', hue='cluster', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    median_life_expect = data['life_expect'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_life_expect, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_life_expect:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('cluster')['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='pop', data=data_grouped, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('How does the population of countries in different clusters compare?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster', loc='upper right', labels=data_grouped['cluster'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
